dow_index","scope":"state","source_url":"https://cmharyanacell.nic.in/cm_window_index","source_name":"CM Grievance Cell (CM Window), Government of Haryana","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Haryana's official grievance redressal and monitoring system, running since 25 December 2014. Register and track complaints online; also lodged in person at DC/SDM offices, e-Disha Kendras and Sub-Division offices."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"grievance","label":"CM Window / CM Grievance Cell contact","value":"01723322500","scope":"state","source_url":"https://cmharyanacell.nic.in/cm_window_index","source_name":"CM Grievance Cell (CM Window), Government of Haryana","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Contact number published on the official CM Window grievance portal. Email: cmgrievanceshry@gmail.com. This is a grievance cell landline, not a toll-free helpline."},{"kind":"url","topic":"grievance","label":"CM Window - official state page","value":"https://www.haryana.gov.in/cm-window/","scope":"state","source_url":"https://www.haryana.gov.in/cm-window/","source_name":"CM Window | Haryana Government","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"The Haryana Government's own page describing CM Window and linking to the grievance portal."},{"kind":"url","topic":"general","label":"Haryana official state portal (homepage)","value":"https://www.haryana.gov.in/","scope":"state","source_url":"https://www.haryana.gov.in/","source_name":"Haryana Government official portal","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15"},{"kind":"url","topic":"general","label":"Haryana districts directory","value":"https://www.haryana.gov.in/districts/","scope":"state","source_url":"https://www.haryana.gov.in/districts/","source_name":"Districts | Haryana Government","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Official listing linking to all 22 district websites: Ambala, Bhiwani, Charkhi Dadri, Faridabad, Fatehabad, Gurugram, Hisar, Jhajjar, Jind, Kaithal, Karnal, Kurukshetra, Mahendragarh, Nuh, Palwal, Panchkula, Panipat, Rewari, Rohtak, Sirsa, Sonipat, Yamunanagar."},{"kind":"url","topic":"general","label":"Antyodaya SARAL - Haryana citizen services portal","value":"https://saralharyana.gov.in/","scope":"state","source_url":"https://saralharyana.gov.in/","source_name":"Antyodaya SARAL Portal, Government of Haryana","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Single window for 600+ Haryana government schemes and services; apply, track application status, download certificates, file and track service tickets."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"general","label":"Antyodaya SARAL helpline","value":"01723968400","scope":"state","source_url":"https://saralharyana.gov.in/","source_name":"Antyodaya SARAL Portal, Government of Haryana","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Operates 7:00 AM - 8:00 PM, Monday to Saturday, excluding government holidays. Email: saral.haryana@gov.in"},{"kind":"phone","topic":"electricity","label":"Electricity complaints (both Haryana DISCOMs)","value":"1912","scope":"state","source_url":"http://www.uhbvn.org.in/web/portal/home","source_name":"Uttar Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam (UHBVN)","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Common no-supply/complaint short code published by both Haryana DISCOMs - UHBVN (north Haryana) and DHBVN (south Haryana).","operator":"All Haryana DISCOMs (1912)"},{"kind":"phone","topic":"electricity","label":"UHBVN electricity complaints, north Haryana (toll free)","value":"18001801550","scope":"state","source_url":"http://www.uhbvn.org.in/web/portal/home","source_name":"Uttar Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam (UHBVN)","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Uttar Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam serves northern Haryana. Also 1912; email 1912@uhbvn.org.in; mobile 9815961912.","operator":"UHBVN","districts":["Ambala","Jhajjar","Kaithal","Karnal","Kurukshetra","Panchkula","Panipat","Rohtak","Sonipat","Yamunanagar"]},{"kind":"email","topic":"electricity","label":"UHBVN electricity complaints email (north Haryana)","value":"1912@uhbvn.org.in","scope":"state","operator":"UHBVN","districts":["Ambala","Jhajjar","Kaithal","Karnal","Kurukshetra","Panchkula","Panipat","Rohtak","Sonipat","Yamunanagar"],"source_url":"https://www.uhbvn.org.in/web/portal/contact-us","source_name":"UHBVN - Contact Us","retrieved_date":"2026-07-16"},{"kind":"phone","topic":"electricity","label":"DHBVN electricity complaints, south Haryana (toll free)","value":"18001804334","scope":"state","source_url":"http://www.dhbvn.org.in/web/portal/home","source_name":"Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam (DHBVN)","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam serves southern Haryana (incl. Gurugram). Also 1912; WhatsApp 8813999708; email 1912@dhbvn.org.in.","operator":"DHBVN","districts":["Bhiwani","Faridabad","Fatehabad","Gurgaon","Hisar","Jind","Mahendragarh","Rewari","Sirsa"]},{"kind":"email","topic":"electricity","label":"DHBVN electricity complaints email (south Haryana)","value":"1912@dhbvn.org.in","scope":"state","operator":"DHBVN","districts":["Bhiwani","Faridabad","Fatehabad","Gurgaon","Hisar","Jind","Mahendragarh","Rewari","Sirsa"],"source_url":"https://www.dhbvn.org.in/web/portal/contact-us","source_name":"DHBVN - Contact Us","retrieved_date":"2026-07-16"},{"kind":"phone","topic":"corruption","label":"Anti-Corruption Bureau helpline (toll free)","value":"1064","scope":"state","source_url":"https://acb.haryana.gov.in/helpline-number/","source_name":"Helpline Number | State Vigilance & Anti Corruption Bureau, Haryana","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Haryana State Vigilance & Anti Corruption Bureau. Also toll free 1800-180-2022; landline 0172-2970057; WhatsApp +91 94178-91064."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"corruption","label":"Anti-Corruption Bureau helpline (alternate toll free)","value":"18001802022","scope":"state","source_url":"https://acb.haryana.gov.in/helpline-number/","source_name":"Helpline Number | State Vigilance & Anti Corruption Bureau, Haryana","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Alternate toll-free number for the Haryana State Vigilance & Anti Corruption Bureau."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"police","label":"STF Haryana - organized crime reporting","value":"01242265900","scope":"state","source_url":"https://hr.erss.in/p/","source_name":"Haryana Emergency Response Support System (ERSS), Haryana Police","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Special Task Force control room, 24x7. Alternate 0124-2265903; WhatsApp 9310138772; email stfharyanacontrolroom@gmail.com."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"emergency","label":"National Emergency Number (ERSS) - Police, Fire & Rescue, Health","value":"112","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.mha.gov.in/en/commoncontent/emergency-response-support-system-erss","source_name":"Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"MHA's single pan-India emergency number: 'ONE INDIA ONE EMERGENCY NUMBER 112', a nationwide unified emergency response system. Works in every State/UT. Corroborated by india.gov.in helpline directory, which lists 112 as the Integrated Helpline (ERSS) covering Police, Fire & Rescue and Health services."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"fire","label":"Fire Helpline","value":"101","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed under 'Emergency Numbers' on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026)."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"ambulance","label":"National Ambulance Service (NAS)","value":"102","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed as 'National Ambulance Service (NAS)' under Emergency Numbers on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026)."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"women","label":"Women Helpline (national, toll-free)","value":"181","scope":"national","source_url":"https://wcd.gov.in/","source_name":"Ministry of Women and Child Development, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Published as 'Women Helpline Toll free No. - 181' directly by the owning ministry (WCD) as a tel: link on its homepage. Also listed on india.gov.in as both 'Women Helpline Number' and 'Domestic Violence Helpline'."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"women","label":"National Commission for Women (NCW) 24x7 Helpline","value":"14490","scope":"national","source_url":"https://ncw.gov.in/","source_name":"National Commission for Women (NCW)","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"NCW's own site states: 'Call the 24x7 NCW helpline at 14490 for immediate assistance and support', and lists 'NCW Women Helpline (14490)' under its Complaint Redressal cells. IMPORTANT: the india.gov.in helpline directory still lists 7827170170 as the 'National Commission for Women Helpline' - that number appears nowhere on ncw.gov.in (not even in raw HTML), so it appears stale and was deliberately omitted in favour of the department's own current number."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"child","label":"Child Helpline (national, toll-free)","value":"1098","scope":"national","source_url":"https://wcd.gov.in/","source_name":"Ministry of Women and Child Development, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Published as 'Child Helpline Toll free No. - 1098' directly by the owning ministry (WCD) as a tel: link on its homepage. Also listed as 'Child Help Line' on india.gov.in."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"senior","label":"Elderline - National Helpline for Senior Citizens (NHSC)","value":"14567","scope":"national","source_url":"https://scw.dosje.gov.in/elderline","source_name":"Department of Social Justice & Empowerment, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Published as 'Elder Helpline: 14567' on the Department of Social Justice & Empowerment's own Elderline site, which the ministry homepage links to as the 'National Helpline for Senior Citizens (NHSC)'. india.gov.in additionally lists a landline 011-20893999 alongside 14567 for the Senior Citizens Helpline."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"grievance","label":"National Consumer Helpline (NCH)","value":"1915","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed as 'National Consumer Helpline (NCH)' on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026). Note: the NCH portal consumerhelpline.gov.in could not be reached at time of research (DNS resolves to an NIC address but the host refused connections / returned 504), so only the number is cited here - not the NCH portal URL."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"cyber","label":"Cyber Crime Helpline (online financial fraud reporting)","value":"1930","scope":"national","source_url":"https://cybercrime.gov.in/","source_name":"National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal, MHA / I4C","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Confirmed on the National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal homepage banner (MHA / Indian Cyber Crime Coordination Centre - I4C), which reads: 'To report online financial fraud, call 1930' and 'register your complaint at cybercrime.gov.in'. Independently corroborated by the india.gov.in helpline directory, which lists 1930 as the Cyber Crime Helpline."},{"kind":"url","topic":"cyber","label":"National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal (file a cybercrime complaint)","value":"https://cybercrime.gov.in/","scope":"national","source_url":"https://cybercrime.gov.in/","source_name":"National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal, MHA / I4C","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Verified live. Ministry of Home Affairs portal for reporting cybercrime; supports anonymous reporting, women/children-related crime, financial fraud and other cybercrime, plus complaint tracking. Nationwide."},{"kind":"url","topic":"grievance","label":"CPGRAMS - Centralised Public Grievance Redress and Monitoring System","value":"https://pgportal.gov.in/","scope":"national","source_url":"https://pgportal.gov.in/","source_name":"Ministry of Personnel, Public Grievances & Pensions, Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Verified live; this is the citizen-facing portal. The site states CPGRAMS is 'an online platform available to the citizens 24x7 to lodge their grievances to the public authorities on any subject related to service delivery... a single portal connected to all the Ministries/Departments of Government of India and States.' Supports tracking by registration ID and an appeal facility. Note: it does not cover RTI matters, subjudice/court matters, or religious matters."},{"kind":"url","topic":"corruption","label":"Central Vigilance Commission - lodge a corruption complaint","value":"https://portal.cvc.gov.in/","scope":"national","source_url":"https://portal.cvc.gov.in/","source_name":"Central Vigilance Commission (CVC), Government of India","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Verified live. CVC's Complaint Management System with a 'Citizen Login', complaint status tracking and a published complaint handling policy. Linked from cvc.gov.in as 'Lodge a complaint'. Covers corruption complaints against central government organisations."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"disaster","label":"Relief Commissioner for Natural Calamities","value":"1070","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026)."},{"kind":"phone","topic":"road","label":"Road Accident Helpline","value":"1073","scope":"national","source_url":"https://www.india.gov.in/directory/helpline","source_name":"National Portal of India (india.gov.in), NIC / MeitY","retrieved_date":"2026-07-15","note":"Listed on the National Portal of India helpline directory (page last reviewed/updated 14 July 2026)."}]}